definition.value: A family of sphingolipids that share a common structural feature, a sphingosine base backbone.
A zwitterionic group obtained by transfer of a proton from the phosphate to the amino group of queuosine 5'-phosphate residue.
An icosatrienoic acid in which the three double bonds have Z configuration and are located at positions 5, 11 and 14.
A zwitterionic group obtained by transfer of a proton from the phosphate to the amino group of 7-aminomethyl-7-carbaguanine 5'-phosphate residue.
A zwitterionic group obtained by transfer of a proton from the phosphate to the amino group of epoxyqueuosine 5'-phosphate residue.
An icosatetraenoic acid in which the four double bonds have Z configuration and are located at positions 5, 11, 14 and 17.
A hexacosenoic acid in which the double bond is located at position 9 and has Z configuration.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as oleoyl and palmitoleoyl respectively.
The pyranose form of D-lyxose.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as oleoyl and palmitoyl respectively.
A 1,2-diacyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the 1- and 2-acyl groups are specified as oleoyl and myristoyl respectively.
A dihydroceramide in which the N-acyl group is specified as octanoyl.
A phytoceramide in which the N-acyl group is specified as octanoyl.
A mixture of products resulting from the amidination of iminodi(ocatmethylene)diamine that contains iminoctadine together with a number of guanidines and polyamines.
A UDP-amino sugar having 2-acetamido-2-deoxy-3-dehydro-alpha-D-glucopyranose as the amino sugar component.
A UDP-amino sugar having 2,3-bis[(3R)-3-hydroxytetradecanoyl]-alpha-D-glucosamine as the amino sugar component.
Any polyunsaturated fatty acid containing 22 carbons and 3 double bonds
An N-acylsphingosine in which the acyl moiety contains 26 carbons and 1 double bond.
A 3-(3-sn-phosphatidyl)-sn-glycerol 1-phosphate in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as oleoyl.
A 1-phosphatidyl-1D-myo-inositol 5-phosphate in which both phosphatidyl acyl groups are specified as octanoyl.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate function of 7-cyano-7-carbaguanine 5'-phosphate residue; major species at 7.3.
A dicarboximide that is phthalimide or derivatives obtained from it by the formal replacement of one or more hydrogens.
An organic anionic group obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate function of inosine 5'-phosphate residue; major species at 7.3.
A member of the class of benzamides obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3,5-dichloro-4-methylbenzamide with the amino group of 3-amino-1-chloro-3-methylpentan-2-one.
A 3,5-dichloro-N-(1-chloro-3-methyl-2-oxopentan-3-yl)-4-methylbenzamide that is the (S)-enantiomer of zoxamide.
A 3,5-dichloro-N-(1-chloro-3-methyl-2-oxopentan-3-yl)-4-methylbenzamide that is the (R)-enantiomer of zoxamide.

A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-ethaboxam.  A fungicide used to control Oomycetes in vines and late potato blight. It is moderately toxic to birds, most aquatic species, honey bees and earthworms.

A member of the class of aromatic amides obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-ethyl-2-(ethylamino)-1,3-thiazole-5-carboxylic acid with the amino group of amino(2-thienyl)acetonitrile.
An N-[cyano(2-thienyl)methyl]-4-ethyl-2-(ethylamino)-1,3-thiazole-5-carboxamide that is the (S)-enantiomer of ethaboxam.
An N-[cyano(2-thienyl)methyl]-4-ethyl-2-(ethylamino)-1,3-thiazole-5-carboxamide that is the (R)-enantiomer of ethaboxam.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-diflumetorim.  Used mainly to control powdery mildew and rust on ornamental crops.
A member of the class of aminopyrimidines that is 5-chloro-6-methylpyrimidin-4-amine in which one of the amino hydrogens is replaced by a 1-[4-(difluoromethoxy)phenyl]propyl group.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-eberconazole. Used (as its nitrate salt) for topical treatment of superficial mycoses.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-fenticonazole. Used (as its nitrate salt) for the treatment of vaginal candidiasis.

An imidazole antifungal agent that is imidazole in which the hydrogen attached to the nitrogen is replaced by a 2,4'-difluorotrityl group. A topical antifungal agent which displays potent broad-spectrum in vitro activity against dermatophytes, filamentous fungi and yeasts.
A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-isoconazole. A broad-spectrum antibacterial drug used (as its nitrate salt) for treatment of dermatomycoses.

A racemate comprising equimolar amounts of (R)- and (S)-sertaconazole. A broad spectrum antifungal with added antipruritic and anti-inflammatory activity used (as its nitrate salt) for treatment of various skin infections.
A 5-chloro-N-{1-[4-(difluoromethoxy)phenyl]propyl}-6-methylpyrimidin-4-amine that is the (R)-enantiomer of diflumetorim.
A 5-chloro-N-{1-[4-(difluoromethoxy)phenyl]propyl}-6-methylpyrimidin-4-amine that has  S configuration.
A sterol ester consiting of (24S)-24-hydroxycholesterol esterified at the 3-hydroxy group.
An organic nitrate salt prepared from equimolar amounts of (R)-econazole and nitric acid.
An organic nitrate salt prepared from equimolar amounts of (S)-econazole and nitric acid.
A 1-{2-(4-chlorobenzyloxy)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole that is the (S)-enantiomer of econazole.
A member of the class of imidazoles that is 1-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)-2-(imidazol-1-yl)ethanol in which the hydroxyl hydrogen is replaced by a 4-chlorobenzyl group.
A ceramide consisting of tetradecasphinganine base having an unspecified fatty acyl group attached to the nitrogen.
A sterol ester that is the 3-linoleoyl derivative of (24S)-24-hydroxycholesterol.
A ceramide consisting of tetradecasphing-4-enine base having an unspecified fatty acyl group attached to the nitrogen.
A 1-{2-(4-chlorobenzyloxy)-2-(2,4-dichlorophenyl)ethyl}imidazole that is the (R)-enantiomer of econazole.
